Experiment 6: Patient Data Transfer System Between Patient and
Hospital Using IoT
Introduction
IoT-based healthcare systems help hospitals monitor patient health conditions remotely. Sensors attached to the
patient collect health data such as temperature, heartbeat, and oxygen level. The collected data is transferred to
hospitals through the internet for continuous monitoring and emergency response.
Objective
The main objective of this system is:
• To monitor patient health remotely
• To transfer patient data to hospitals in real time
• To reduce hospital visits
• To provide quick medical response during emergencies
Components Used
• Arduino Uno / ESP32
• Temperature Sensor
• Pulse Sensor
• Wi-Fi Module
• Buzzer
• Cloud Platform (ThingSpeak/Blynk)
• Internet Connection
Working Principle
The sensors continuously monitor patient health conditions. The Arduino or ESP32 reads the sensor values and
sends the data to the hospital server using Wi-Fi modules.
Examples:
• Temperature sensor measures body temperature.
• Pulse sensor measures heart rate.
• Cloud platform stores patient data.
• Doctors can monitor patient health remotely.
• Alerts are generated during abnormal conditions.
